tips-dataset-1 = If you're on fire, hit the alert and drop to the ground. Rolling might save your hide.
tips-dataset-2 = You can view and edit all keybindings used in-game at any time through the Options menu.
tips-dataset-3 = You can access the in-game guidebook through the escape menu, or by pressing Numpad 0 by default.
tips-dataset-4 = Some objects have guide entries associated with them, which you can view by examining them and clicking the question mark icon.
tips-dataset-5 = Pre-war artifacts can develop strange permanent effects when tampered with. Sometimes useful. Sometimes fatal.
tips-dataset-6 = You can avoid slipping on most puddles by walking. However, strong industrial chemicals will still put you on your back.
tips-dataset-7 = Mutated plants can be processed into powerful and valuable medicines.
tips-dataset-8 = Cleaning and collecting spilled liquids preserves valuable reagents.
tips-dataset-9 = Drain grates in old ruins rapidly consume nearby liquids, including blood.
tips-dataset-10 = Certain experimental chems can awaken intelligence in animals when injected. Results are unpredictable.
tips-dataset-11 = Loaded mousetraps are extremely effective against small pests.
tips-dataset-12 = Fire extinguishers can be filled with nearly any liquid.
tips-dataset-13 = Some reagents have unique effects when applied by touch, such as through spray bottles or foam.
tips-dataset-14 = Step away from the wasteland once in a while. Burnout kills faster than radiation.
tips-dataset-15 = You can use the Activate in World keybind, E by default, to interact with objects while your hands are full.
tips-dataset-16 = Common sense prevents more gunfights than armor ever will.
tips-dataset-17 = Every other drifter, raider, and settler you meet is another real person.
tips-dataset-18 = If your settlement relies on a generator, guard it well. Power is life.
tips-dataset-19 = Maintain backup generators or solar rigs in case your main power source fails.
tips-dataset-20 = Chemicals do not react while stored safely in proper equipment.
tips-dataset-21 = Respect the barkeep. Caps are easier earned than teeth.
tips-dataset-22 = Slow down vehicles when traveling rough terrain for better control.
tips-dataset-23 = Certain medical chems purge toxins from your bloodstream while metabolizing.
tips-dataset-24 = Most wastelanders carry basic emergency supplies. Check your gear.
tips-dataset-25 = Generators are prime sabotage targets. Plan for redundancy.
tips-dataset-26 = Electrical surges and EMP bursts can fry electronics. Drop them if needed.
tips-dataset-27 = You can add labels to items using a hand labeler.
tips-dataset-28 = Heavy combat armor is far more effective against melee attacks than light clothing.
tips-dataset-29 = As a ghost, you can use the Verb Menu to orbit and follow any entity.
tips-dataset-30 = As an antagonist, you may be assigned to eliminate rivals, including other hostile operatives.
tips-dataset-31 = Encrypted radios allow secure communication between allies.
tips-dataset-32 = Compromising enemy communications can provide valuable intelligence. The same can happen to you.
tips-dataset-33 = A compact toolkit is versatile and invaluable in emergencies.
tips-dataset-34 = Light tactical vests are affordable and offer solid protection.
tips-dataset-35 = Certain explosive creatures may obey their handler but will detonate if killed.
tips-dataset-36 = Carrying suspicious chems invites unwanted attention.
tips-dataset-37 = Hidden sabotage devices often make noise over time. Conceal them carefully.
tips-dataset-38 = Plasma burns hot, spreads fast, and poisons those who inhale it.
tips-dataset-39 = Revived creatures can serve as deadly distractions.
tips-dataset-40 = Tampering with batteries and volatile compounds can cause violent explosions.
tips-dataset-41 = If you're part of a raider squad or strike team, stick together. Teamwork wins firefights.
tips-dataset-42 = Communication is key. Use your radio to coordinate.
tips-dataset-43 = Stealth often keeps you breathing longer than brute force.
tips-dataset-44 = Destroying communication towers makes it harder for enemies to coordinate.
tips-dataset-45 = Examine your radio to see available channels and how to speak in them.
tips-dataset-46 = Always carry a GPS when traveling far from your settlement.
tips-dataset-47 = In zero gravity environments, weapons or tools can provide minor directional thrust.
tips-dataset-48 = Salvaging scrap and ore fuels construction and advanced crafting.
tips-dataset-49 = Grappling tools make traversing ruins and wreckage far safer.
tips-dataset-50 = Trade routes provide rare weapons and construction materials.
tips-dataset-51 = Tip #51 does not exist and never has. Ignore rumors.
tips-dataset-52 = Traders can supply specialized gear that is otherwise difficult to acquire.
tips-dataset-53 = Power armor frames make hauling heavy scrap much easier.
tips-dataset-54 = Maintain a surplus of materials. Tomorrow may not be kind.
tips-dataset-55 = Gambling caps rarely ends well.
tips-dataset-56 = In emergencies, traders can provide additional firepower.
tips-dataset-57 = A circular saw can shorten a shotgun for easier concealment.
tips-dataset-58 = Experiment with drinks. Some hit harder than bullets.
tips-dataset-59 = Crossbreeding crops can improve yield and potency.
tips-dataset-60 = Commit to your gimmick. Nobody remembers half measures.
tips-dataset-61 = Improvised slipping tools are everywhere if you're creative.
tips-dataset-62 = Kitchen knives double as weapons in desperate times.
tips-dataset-63 = Poisoned food is effective but risky.
tips-dataset-64 = Breaking your personal code has consequences.
tips-dataset-65 = Negotiation can reduce punishment during disputes.
tips-dataset-66 = Coordinate with allies to avoid chaos in combat.
tips-dataset-67 = Suspicion alone is not proof.
tips-dataset-68 = Forensics tools allow tracking via fingerprints and fibers.
tips-dataset-69 = Portable barriers can block gas while allowing movement.
tips-dataset-70 = Improvised explosives often cause friendly casualties.
tips-dataset-71 = A lit welding tool can repair cracked windows and metal structures.
tips-dataset-72 = Powered wiring can electrify metal barriers.
tips-dataset-73 = Double check containment systems. Mistakes are catastrophic.
tips-dataset-74 = Uranium infused materials resist radiation.
tips-dataset-75 = Leaders are high priority targets.
tips-dataset-76 = Critical faction items should never leave your possession.
tips-dataset-77 = Authority abused leads to rebellion.
tips-dataset-78 = Staying mobile reduces the chance of ambush.
tips-dataset-79 = Experimenting with artifacts can uncover powerful effects.
tips-dataset-80 = Upgraded components significantly improve machine performance.
tips-dataset-81 = Synthetic allies can be built with the right knowledge and parts.
tips-dataset-82 = Overdosing patients can kill them faster than their wounds.
tips-dataset-83 = Medical pods can treat many forms of damage.
tips-dataset-84 = Some species are vulnerable to extreme cold.
tips-dataset-85 = Health analyzers require charged batteries. Upgrade when possible.
tips-dataset-86 = Not every chem needs to be practical. Some are just fun.
tips-dataset-87 = Sedatives can non-lethally subdue hostile targets.
tips-dataset-88 = Don't be afraid to ask for help in character or through LOOC.
tips-dataset-89 = Playing only to win will drain the fun quickly.
tips-dataset-90 = Cooperation accomplishes more than isolation.
tips-dataset-91 = The nuclear device itself cannot be destroyed. Secure its control component instead.
tips-dataset-92 = Ruins and abandoned facilities contain randomized loot each round.
tips-dataset-93 = We were all new once. Guide fresh faces when you can.
tips-dataset-94 = Heavy protective suits provide moderate cold resistance.
tips-dataset-95 = Emergency protective gear can save your life in hostile environments.
tips-dataset-96 = Improvised weapons can mean the difference between life and death.
tips-dataset-97 = Spears can be tipped with chemicals to inject targets.
tips-dataset-98 = Reinforced materials increase spear durability and damage.
tips-dataset-99 = Thrown spears hit harder but may break.
tips-dataset-100 = Toxin damage is difficult to treat and effective in combat.
tips-dataset-101 = Bolas can slow fleeing targets.
tips-dataset-102 = Fuel tanks can be modified into crude flamethrowers.
tips-dataset-103 = Some roles have alternate outfits available.
tips-dataset-104 = Speed decides most fights.
tips-dataset-105 = Just because someone is not hostile at the start does not mean they will stay loyal.
tips-dataset-106 = Protective gas masks block flashes and welding glare.
tips-dataset-107 = Explosives require skill and planning.
tips-dataset-108 = Firing weapons or spraying extinguishers can provide slight movement in zero gravity.
tips-dataset-109 = Drag someone onto yourself to search or strip them.
tips-dataset-110 = Drag yourself onto a table or debris to climb it.
tips-dataset-111 = Hold CTRL and right click to precisely reposition dragged items.
tips-dataset-112 = Cooperation and deception can reduce punishment.
tips-dataset-113 = Fire spreads through contact.
tips-dataset-114 = Structural breaches create violent winds that pull objects and people.
tips-dataset-115 = Burns can cauterize wounds and stop bleeding.
tips-dataset-116 = Untreated bleeding will kill you.
tips-dataset-117 = Clothing can be cut into cloth for crafting bandages.
tips-dataset-118 = Sharp tools allow butchering of animals and materials.
tips-dataset-119 = Most explosives have adjustable timers.
tips-dataset-120 = Explosive creatures can sometimes be stunned before detonation.
tips-dataset-121 = You can click item names in the right click menu to pick them up.
tips-dataset-122 = The wasteland is community built. Contribute if you can.
tips-dataset-123 = Spilled liquids can slow pursuers.
tips-dataset-124 = Some melee weapons have very fast attack speeds.
tips-dataset-125 = Hydraulic spreaders can pry open sealed doors.
tips-dataset-126 = Certain mutated beings can consume blood to restore blood volume inefficiently.
tips-dataset-127 = Humans should not drink blood.
tips-dataset-128 = Your body can only process so many chems at once.
tips-dataset-129 = Welding without eye protection damages your vision.
tips-dataset-130 = Zombies are especially vulnerable to heat and lasers.
tips-dataset-131 = Glass shards can be reforged into usable sheets.
tips-dataset-132 = Right click a player and use the heart icon to assess injuries.
tips-dataset-133 = Some creatures may display unexpected intelligence.
tips-dataset-134 = Flickering lights and pressure warnings can signal structural danger.
tips-dataset-135 = You can alt-click food to eat it without picking it up.
